<P>&nbsp;</P>
<P>Each psionicist has a set number of PSPs that he may use each day. This number 
is determined based on the character's Wisdom, Intelligence, and Constitution 
scores.</P>
<P>At 1st level, a psionicist begins with a number of PSPs based on his Wisdom 
score, indexed in the previous table, plus his Intelligence and Constitution 
modifiers. </P>
<P>So, for example, Jackal has C 16, I 14, W 16. At 1st level, Jackal has 22+3 
(C) +2 (I) = 27 PSPs.</P>
<P>At each level above 1st, a psionicist gains 10 + his Wisdom modifier additional 
PSPs. So, at 2nd level, Jackal gains another 10+3 = 13 additional PSPs, for 
a total of 40 PSPs.</P>
<P>Even though a psionicist may not have access to the Telepathy Discipline, he 
still is able to defend himself when attacked psionically. As he gains levels, 
he automatically gains access to additional Defense Modes (Constructs) as shown 
on the Class Table.</P>
